Program: Discovery
Title: What remains to be discovered - secrets of life
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jryb7
Last Broadcast Date: 29 January 2003
Fourth in a series investigating the secrets of life. Just how did life begin? Could the incredible complexities of even the most basic lifeforms we know have begun as chance chemistry? Exactly what is life? Presented by Professor Bob May.